The explosion in a downtown area of 
Springfield, 90 miles west of Boston, blew out all windows in a 
three-block radius, leaving three more buildings damaged beyond repair.

Police Sgt. John Delaney described the devastation left by the gas blast as looking like a 'missile strike.'

Massachusetts Lt. Gov. Tim Murray said it was 'a miracle' no one was killed.

Area resident Wayne Davis, who lives a block away, said he felt his apartment building shake.

