'I was laying down in bed, and I started feeling the building shaking and creaking,' he said.

The Navy veteran said the boom from the explosion was louder than anything he'd ever heard, including the sound of a jet landing on an aircraft carrier.

Another Springfield resident, who witnessed the blast from a barbershop, told WWLP-TV he heard a loud explosion that knocked him off his feet. He said he looked up the street and saw one building severely damaged.

Firefighters say they're investigating how the blast happened.

